window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>New York Times </i></b><b>best-selling author Kay Hooper is back with a brand-new, thrilling paranormal suspense novel in the Bishop/Special Crimes Unit series.</b></p> <p>The small town of Salem has been quiet for months - or so Bishop and his elite Special Crimes Unit believe. But then Hollis Templeton and Diana Hayes receive a warning in Diana’s eerie “gray time” between the world of the living and the realm of the dead that a twisted killer is stalking Salem, bent on destroying in the most bloody and horrifying way possible the five families that founded the town.</p> <p>The stakes are high, especially for new friends Nellie Cavendish and Finn Deverell, both members of the Five, and this time Bishop and his wife, Miranda, will lead the team to hunt down a vicious killer and uncover a dark and ancient curse haunting Salem.</p>"; 
